New Records: Ruben Trumpelmann became the first player in T20I history to take two wickets with the first two balls of a match
Key Match Events: Namibia and Oman ended their innings at the identical score of 109, necessitating the one-over eliminator
Namibia's Gerhard Erasmus and David Wiese took charge in the Super Over, smashing 21 runs to set a formidable target for Oman
Oman's response fell short as they managed only 10 runs in the Super Over
Post-Match Reflections: Namibia's David Wiese expressed his satisfaction with the team's performance and the win in the Super Over
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the second Super Over in T20 World Cup history, following the first-ever between New Zealand and Sri Lanka in Kandy in 2012
